name: Lace Closure
description: Many who wear sew in or bonded weaves, use the Lace Closures to cover the top area of the head where the weft hair ( track hair, weaving hair ) is bonded/sewn down. They are used to cover the area that is know to many as the "leave-out". Those who are very familiar to wearing weaves know that the most important part of weaving is to make sure the area at the front hairline & crown area are well blended. They can also be used with various other weaving methods. You can apply them with weaving thread or with liquid/tape adhesives. No one will ever know it is not your natural hair growing out of your scalp!

name: Lace Frontals
description: Want to look as if hair is growing from your scalp? Tired of trying to blend your natural hair in with your expensive Remy weaving hair, in order to cover up tracks? Is your natural hair becoming brittle and unhealthy by over processing? Want to be able to able to comb your hair in any style, whether it is a part on the side, a part in the middle, twists in the front, or  a pony tail straight back?
